Step 1. Download nodejs from https://nodejs.org/en/download/
Step 2. Install nodejs as an administrator.
Step 3. Open command promt and set application folder path. 
    > Change the directory using CD command.
    > The current directory would expect the source folder.
Step 4. Install angular cli using command $ 'npm i -g @angular/cli latest'
Step 5. To execute the application use $ 'ng serve --o' command. 
(This command will run the application by opening a default browser)

Video Link : https://www.screencast.com/t/PIZQ7p4L6QKZ


